node.text:
The Amazon gurus will hate me for this but Skeptics listen up- you were right.

You can’t get rich overnight with Amazon.

There is not 10k in 30 days- at least not in profits

“Done for you” shops make no sense- if they can build a wildly profitable store, why not build it for themselves and make profits every month instead of a measly one-time payment from you?

No- this doesn’t work. The only way to succeed with Amazon is following the normal path of any business:

Learn the craft, build a skillset, gain knowledge and work on it until it works for you.

You can do it yourself or you can do it with help, both are fine, the only difference is how much time and money you lose due to rookie mistakes.

If you want to build an Amazon business and have guidance from step 0 until the very end, then 

Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity

They’ll show you how Amazon FBA really works, no fluff, no flashy flexing, no outrageous promises. Just a real education that’s gonna help you build a business that lasts.

node.text:
Would you quit your 40h job to work 80h for yourself?

If you want to start your own Amazon business because you want to work less and make more, I have bad news.

Running your own business doesn’t automatically mean that you’ll work less.

Especially in the beginning, you have to put in more time and effort to get things going.

It can feel like an uphill battle.

Maybe you can’t find the right products to sell...maybe shipments are late…

There are all kinds of problems.

But once you reach the tipping point, it all pays off.

Once you’ve overcome the initial hardships, you’ll start to get time freedom.

Because now your business is working for you.

If you want to get started on Amazon and make it a business that’s working for you without the initial hardships, head over and 

follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity
follow 👉@bjkuniversity

...to learn from the pros.

node.text:
You don’t need to have it all figured out.

It’s okay if you don’t know everything.

In fact, it’s better to fail forward than to be paralyzed by fear.

The only thing that’s not okay is pretending you are big shot just because you watched some YouTube videos…

Everyone can do that. Having free resources doesn’t automatically equal success.

I only started becoming successful after I did three things in my life:

I stopped repeating the same mistakes by learning from them
I put in the work and bettered myself 
I learned from professionals who already had achieved what I wanted to achieve

And now, I don’t make unnecessary mistakes anymore, but guess what, sometimes I still fail. 

Yet, when I do, I know how to deal with it and I know whom I can ask for help.

If you wanna succeed with Amazon FBA without making my dumb mistakes first, 

Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity

And they’ll show you how it’s done.

node.text:
You don’t need 100 ways to achieve something…
You don’t need 100 strategies, methods, and skills.

One proven way is enough. 

In fact, most people try to do too much.

They start a business and try to implement 3 business models at once…

They want to launch hundreds of products…

And confuse and overwhelm themselves in the process.

I’m a strong believer in the KISS model - Keep it simple, stupid.

The moment I started to only focus on my Amazon business, I got way better results.

If you want to start a business, don’t try to do everything. Focus on one thing at a time.

And if you want to start an Amazon business...

Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity
Follow 👉@bjkuniversity

And they’ll get you started.
